article.headline: Green Bay blisters Valpo to clinch share of Horizon title
article.linkText: No. 12 Green Bay seals share of Horizon crown
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. --  Lydia Bauer scored 17 points and Julie Wojta scored 16 to lead No. 12 Green Bay past Valparaiso 72-36 Thursday night, enabling the Phoenix to clinch a share of their 14th consecutive Horizon League championship.

The Phoenix (24-1, 14-1) raced to a 31-11 halftime lead.

Stephanie Sension added 12 points and Wojta grabbed 10 rebounds and contributed five assists. Green Bay has won four in a row since its only loss of the season at Detroit.

Tabitha Gerardot had nine points to lead Valparaiso (8-18, 4-11).
